H0.text: What is the name given to the vertical groove that runs between the top lip and the nose. Nasolabial Sulcus

H1.text: What is the name given to the vertical groove that runs between the top lip and the nose. Labionasal Fissure

H2.text: What is the name given to the vertical groove that runs between the top lip and the nose. Interlabial Groove

H3.text: What is the name given to the vertical groove that runs between the top lip and the nose. Filtrum

A4.text: It is also known as the nasolabial sulcus.
